<br>In preparation for the upcoming singing contest, the school', CHAR(39), 's singing club wishes to use Sousuke Kagura', CHAR(39), 's song "Cloudy Days," but Kagura is reluctant to grant his permission. The song requires someone with a three-octave range to sing it and he believes that only a VOCALOID can meet the standards. He allows for the club to use his song on the condition that they can find someone who possesses that vocal range to properly sing it.<br>
